{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcc06cae81d148616b292e", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 60, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fee2b295b085ab6ebbc"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64634cba0194a6ffd0fd1034", "title": "NEET 2023 (All India)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "<p>Given below are two statements: one labelled as Assertion <strong>A</strong> and other is labelled as Reason <strong>R</strong>:</p><p>Assertion <strong>A:&nbsp;</strong>A reaction can have zero activation energy</p><p>Reason <strong>R:&nbsp;</strong>The minimum extra amount of energy absorbed by reactant molecules so that their energy becomes equal to threshold value, is called activation energy.</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "wrSxO", "text": "<strong>A</strong>&nbsp;is false but <strong>R</strong> is true.", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "U4pCL", "text": "Both <strong>A</strong> and <strong>R</strong> are true and <strong>R</strong> is the correct explanation of <strong>A</strong>.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "ASygD", "text": "Both <strong>A</strong> and <strong>R</strong> are true and <strong>R</strong> is not the correct explanation of <strong>A</strong>.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "zeUvo", "text": "<strong>A</strong>&nbsp;is true but <strong>R</strong> is false.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<blockquote><p>Activation energy is defined as the minimum amount of extra energy required by a reacting molecule to get converted into a product.&nbsp; If<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> , then according to Arrhenius equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>Ae</mi><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>RT</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>Ae</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> . This implies that every collision results into a chemical reaction which cannot be true. So, a reaction cannot have zero activation energy.</p></blockquote>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ72744024", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["615f0cf69476412f48314dac", "616057040283de43c87e3e16", "61bb58281213731910ea0b71", "6160579d0283de43c87e3e1f", "61964f94a5a526011886801e", "61c055f6e8ce0dc8a5c62d34", "61a8a2cce8ce0dc8a5c62d2e", "6160577e0283de43c87e3e1c", "616057210283de43c87e3e19", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352c", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd8", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7e", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625c", "61964ff3a5a5260118868022", "64d50c263df7f4a7f3017f70", "66b79b89d4b564dfab4f94d0", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc12", "67fa602f4468eb1307ceb0ae", "6807d350647479b8e869647a"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616024d6df9e5dfc7433de43", "616024d5853f399f4e180150", "61e7bd81ea0910c9b55ac9eb", "616024d3211ca7bc5ace4831", "61bb822d43b95f139752eee8", "61964caa6f1eeafa19c56b32", "61964ca92a5fb01732e20cff", "61c089bdac26500699dd06b5", "616024d4b1349be0edb49c08", "616024d734da0acf9df2195c", "629109da1c71941361294635", "62962117b32f906fc6ce0b9a", "629f38febbfbb41f88beb7cd", "629f3a84342447bcc13d9a0b", "64eb06d13118f713ecfef125", "66d58542a75f05ee8564f5be", "67921d731d5b5072da5e9b28", "67fdff42378e1624ea7b6947", "68091fe03a10446a207fdbd2"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "6